# 📦 Package Name Change Guide — Yugma App

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Your app currently has **two names** in use:
> - **Package/Bundle ID**: `com.yugmamatch` (Android)
> - **iOS Bundle ID**: `org.reactjs.native.example.Yugma` (default — likely needs updating too)
> - **RN App Name**: `Yugma` (in `app.json`)
> - **NPM Package Name**: `VivahSetu` (in `package.json` — leftover from old name)

---

## What's Your New Package Name?

Before starting, decide on your **new package name**. For example:
- `com.newcompany.yugma`
- `com.yugma.app`
- etc.

Tell me the new name and I can make all the changes for you!

---

## ✅ Complete Checklist of Files to Change

### 1. Android — Code & Build Files

| # | File | What to Change | Current Value |
|---|------|---------------|---------------|
| 1 | [build.gradle](file:///Users/vikalpnimesh/Desktop/Matpatra/Y/Yugma/android/app/build.gradle#L80) | `namespace` | `com.yugmamatch` |
| 2 | [build.gradle](file:///Users/vikalpnimesh/Desktop/Matpatra/Y/Yugma/android/app/build.gradle#L82) | `applicationId` | `com.yugmamatch` |
| 3 | [MainActivity.kt](file:///Users/vikalpnimesh/Desktop/Matpatra/Y/Yugma/android/app/src/main/java/com/yugmamatch/MainActivity.kt#L1) | `package` declaration | `com.yugmamatch` |
| 4 | [MainApplication.kt](file:///Users/vikalpnimesh/Desktop/Matpatra/Y/Yugma/android/app/src/main/java/com/yugmamatch/MainApplication.kt#L1) | `package` declaration | `com.yugmamatch` |
| 5 | **Folder structure** | Move Kotlin files to match new package | `android/app/src/main/java/com/yugmamatch/` → e.g. `android/app/src/main/java/com/newname/` |

> [!WARNING]
> The **folder path** under `android/app/src/main/java/` **must match** the new package name. For example, if the new package is `com.example.yugma`, the files must be at `android/app/src/main/java/com/example/yugma/`.

---

### 2. Android — Firebase

| # | File | What to Change | Current Value |
|---|------|---------------|---------------|
| 6 | [google-services.json](file:///Users/vikalpnimesh/Desktop/Matpatra/Y/Yugma/android/app/google-services.json#L12) | `package_name` | `com.yugmamatch` |

> [!CAUTION]
> **DO NOT just edit this file manually!** You must:
> 1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/) → Project `comyugmamatch`
> 2. Add a **new Android app** with the new package name
> 3. Download the **new `google-services.json`** and replace the existing one
> 4. (Optional) Delete the old Android app entry from Firebase

---

