## 🔥 External Services to Update

### Firebase Console
- **URL**: https://console.firebase.google.com/
- **Action**: Add new Android app with new package name → download new `google-services.json`
- **Action**: Add new iOS app with new bundle ID → download new `GoogleService-Info.plist` (you don't currently have one — you'll need it if using Firebase on iOS)

### Google Play Console
- ⚠️ **You CANNOT change the package name of a published app on Google Play**
- If already published with `com.yugmamatch`, you must create a **new app listing**

### Apple Developer / App Store Connect
- Update the **Bundle ID** in your Apple Developer account
- If already registered, create a new App ID with the new bundle identifier

### Google Sign-In
- Update the OAuth client in [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/) with the new package name / bundle ID
- For Android: Update the SHA-1 fingerprint association with the new package name

### RevenueCat (if you add it back)
- No current RevenueCat config found, but if you re-add it, register the new package name/bundle ID there

---

## 📋 Summary — Quick Priority Order

```
1. Decide new package name (e.g., com.newcompany.yugma)
2. Update Firebase Console → get new google-services.json
3. Update Android files (build.gradle, Kotlin files, folder structure)
4. Update iOS bundle identifier (via Xcode)
5. Update app.json and package.json
6. Update Google Cloud Console (OAuth / Sign-In)
7. Update Google Play Console / App Store Connect
8. Clean build → test
```

---

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Tell me your **new desired package name** and whether you also want to change the **app display name**, and I can make all the code changes for you automatically!
